The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of Neural Architecture Search (NAS) algorithm, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper proposes a sample-based NAS framework combined with Bayesian Optimization, which involves using a sampler and a learnable embedding extractor. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Among these sub-categories, cs.LG is the most likely one as it is the most general sub-category that covers a wide range of machine learning topics, including NAS. The other sub-categories are also relevant as they involve topics such as computer vision, optimization, and control, which are relevant to the proposed method.
